{
  "texts": [
    "An affine expanding Ricci soliton is of gradient type if and only if N ≃ R n is abelian and ρ takes values in O(n).Proof.",
    "Assume that X = ∇f for some smooth function f ∈ C ∞.",
    "By Ansatz 3.1, the structure group of the bundle π: M → B reduces to Aut ±1 (N), thus M is a Lie group bundle (vector bundle in case N is abelian), and there is a well-defined identity (zero) section.",
    "From Ansatz 3.1, (iii) we also know that X is vertical and it restricts to a soliton vector field X b of each fibre M b.",
    "In particular, f is horizontally constant."
  ]
}